
Overview of verb hasten

The verb hasten has 4 senses (first 4 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (7) rush, hasten, hurry, look sharp, festinate -- (act or move at high speed; "We have to rush!"; "hurry--it's late!")
2. (6) rush, hotfoot, hasten, hie, speed, race, pelt along, rush along, cannonball along, bucket along, belt along, step on it -- (move fast; "He rushed down the hall to receive his guests"; "The cars raced down the street")
3. (2) expedite, hasten -- (speed up the progress of; facilitate; "This should expedite the process")
4. (1) induce, stimulate, rush, hasten -- (cause to occur rapidly; "the infection precipitated a high fever and allergic reactions")
